bug.short_desc: Replace # Hints with @ Hints for the Compiler

long_desc.thetext:
This is a follow-up from bug#4615.
The old # hints (#ignore, #require, ...) should be replaced by corresponding @ hints (@ignore, @require, ...), so there is a single syntax for meta information, all based on JSDoc comments. This will simplify code, maitenance and further extensions.
All # hints have been replace by @ hints, in the framework classes, the apps, components and skeletons. #-hints will trigger a deprecation warning. Manual has been updated.

Please also grep for occurrences of #asset in tool/ (in code and comments) and replace with @asset where appropriate.
Two of those were in string messages, which I fixed in master with 044a6079. While the deprecated syntax still works, it certainly makes sense to switch to the preferred syntax throughout the code base (unless it's specifically about the legacy #asset syntax, of course).

(In reply to comment #3) > Please also grep for occurrences of #asset in tool/ (in code and comments) and > replace with @asset where appropriate.
Fixed, thanks.
master: 52d6bf6

@ignore hints don't work with "wrapped" external libraries. There's no way to suppress
- Warning: jsdtest.Jquery (9815): Unknown global symbol used: module.exports - Warning: jsdtest.Jquery (9828): Unknown global symbol used: define
with @ignore where it works just fine with #ignore. See the attachment.
Also note that this is just a warning in the case of single-file build. In partial build case these unknown globals break the build at package verification step.

I've made a commit that fixes the attached example. Give it a go.
If you come across any more issues please open dedicated bugs for them, as this one ("Replace # .. with @ ...") is actually done.
